  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Risk-on sentiment is driving a coordinated move across assets as US-Iran diplomatic hopes reduce geopolitical risk premium, with oil declining, dollar weakening to 6-week lows, and Asian equities hitting 6-week highs. The relief rally is broadening beyond equities into crypto ($1.1B institutional inflows) and away from safe havens, while Japan's strong machine orders data adds to global growth optimism.",
    "regimeImpact": "The bear market oversold relief rally assessment remains intact and is actually strengthening as geopolitical risk reduction and dollar weakness create more favorable conditions for risk assets to continue their bounce.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR cash-secured put ladder closely as ETH approaches $2,400 resistance with strong institutional demand but faces technical rejection risk",
      "Consider reducing short book exposure as relief rally broadens with improving risk sentiment and weakening dollar creating headwinds for bearish positions",
      "Maintain Maturity sector overweight but watch for rotation into Growth as geopolitical risks ease and institutional crypto flows suggest increased risk appetite"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Dollar hitting 6-week lows signals meaningful shift in risk sentiment that could extend relief rally across all risk assets including crypto.",
      "Oil declining on Iran talk hopes removes a key stagflation risk (our $100 threshold) and reduces input cost pressures.",
      "Crypto seeing $1.1B institutional inflows with Bitcoin whale accumulation at 2-month highs suggests smart money positioning for continued upside.",
      "Asian equities at 6-week highs confirms global nature of relief rally, reducing tail risk of isolated US market bounce."
    ]
